      "text": "We are told that we live in the Information Age, yet teachers in schools are still being told what information our children need to know. With masses of information readily available to any child in their natural environment, from another human, or technology, the question emerges, \"Why are we still limiting what our children could know?\" There is a sense that this focus on knowledge is for control, domination and a desire for certainty."
