      "text": "What if this unknowing could be viewed differently? What if the problem is not that what we thought would be is not so, but that the chasing of knowing is wrong? What if we were more focused on being with the process and experiencing awe; the awakening of wonder to moments of eureka?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "edd0690c7f6d20be",
      "text": "What if instead of some external authority determining what we think, what we know, what we do, we focused on the internal authority of our own thought? David Bohm explains that thought is participatory, both a determinant and determined by the whole. We cannot split ourselves from the whole but we can choose not to be limited by our immediate, perceived whole. We can remember that we are [[Limitless Energy]] that is constantly revealing itself as a part of the [[Natural Order]]."
